definitions.definition: The process or act of selecting .
examples: The large number of good candidates made selection difficult.
My final selection was a 1934 Chateau Lafite .

definitions.definition: A variety of items taken from a larger collection.
examples: I've brought a selection of fine cheeses to go with your wine.
For my next selection , I'll play Happy Birthday in F-sharp minor.

definitions.definition: A set of data obtained from a database using a query .
The ability of predicates to determine the semantic content of their arguments .
A list of items on which user operations will take place.
A unary operation that denotes a subset of a relation .
The free selection before survey of crown land in some Australian colonies under land legislation introduced in the 1860s.

subdefinitions.definition: A plot of land, or farm, thus selected.

definitions.definition: The stage of a genetic algorithm in which individual genomes are chosen from a population for later breeding .
